message.content:
We have to “calculate the final tax expense item” by adding up the “tax_amount” from every sale transaction. In these records the only entries that carry a “tax_amount” value are the Sale‐transactions. (Other transactions such as Purchases, Expenses, Interest and Depreciation do not record any tax amount.) 

Step 1. Identify every sale transaction and extract its tax component. In our table the Sale rows are as follows (showing the tax_amount from each):

• Sale20240105004: tax_amount = 73,151.62  
• Sale20240107006: tax_amount = 107,979.34  
• Sale20240111008: tax_amount = 37,480.09  
• Sale20240114011: tax_amount = 66,634.33  
• Sale20240117015: tax_amount = 57,377.80  
• Sale20240118016: tax_amount = 107,823.34  
• Sale20240119018: tax_amount = 33,440.41  
• Sale20240121020: tax_amount = 33,221.79  
• Sale20240125022: tax_amount = 33,741.52  
• Sale20240128026: tax_amount = 35,359.45  
• Sale20240130027: tax_amount = 104,591.59  
• Sale20240131029: tax_amount = 70,872.92  
• Sale20240201031: tax_amount = 99,980.23  
• Sale20240203034: tax_amount = 101,420.10  
• Sale20240204037: tax_amount = 52,848.01  

Step 2. Sum these tax amounts step‐by‐step:

1. 73,151.62  
2. 73,151.62 + 107,979.34 = 181,130.96  
3. 181,130.96 + 37,480.09 = 218,611.05  
4. 218,611.05 + 66,634.33 = 285,245.38  
5. 285,245.38 + 57,377.80 = 342,623.18  
6. 342,623.18 + 107,823.34 = 450,446.52  
7. 450,446.52 + 33,440.41 = 483,886.93  
8. 483,886.93 + 33,221.79 = 517,108.72  
9. 517,108.72 + 33,741.52 = 550,850.24  
10. 550,850.24 + 35,359.45 = 586,209.69  
11. 586,209.69 + 104,591.59 = 690,801.28  
12. 690,801.28 + 70,872.92 = 761,674.20  
13. 761,674.20 + 99,980.23 = 861,654.43  
14. 861,654.43 + 101,420.10 = 963,074.53  
15. 963,074.53 + 52,848.01 = 1,011,922.54  

Step 3. The final “Tax Expense” is therefore 1,011,922.54.

Thus, we report the answer in the required JSON format as follows:

------------------------------------------------

{
  "solution": {
    "Tax Expense": "1011922.54"
  }
}

This is the final computed tax expense item for the income statement.
